Step-by-Step Guide: Creating and Using a Python venv
Follow these steps to set up a clean workspace for your Python project.

1. Create the Environment
Open your terminal in your project folder and run the following command. This creates a folder named venv that will hold all your local libraries.
command: python -m venv venv

2. Activate the Environment
You must "enter" the environment every time you start a new terminal session.

Windows (PowerShell): .\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

macOS / Linux: source venv/bin/activate

3. Install Your Tools
Now that you see (venv) in your terminal, any library you install stays inside this project.
command: pip install pyside6

4. Leave the Environment
When you are done working, just type:

Bash
deactivate
